title: Wait, what’s going on in this photo?
text:
A man standing at urinal at Hong Kong Airport saw a hand pop through the wall. Source: Supplied 
YOU’VE got to hand it to this traveller — he has captured a unique photo! 
The passenger got the surprise of his life during a visit to a public bathroom at Hong Kong International Airport. 
He had approached a urinal and looked up only to see something that appeared to be a human hand poking out of the wall. 
The baffled man shared the photo on the popular local forum Hong Kong Golden , where perplexed users quickly weighed in on what they suspected was going on in the strange snap. Yep, that looks like a human hand. Source: Supplied 
Suggestions range from it being a prank, to a maintenance worker repairing a sensor, and one even suggested that the flush was being manually operated by an employee. 
news.com.au has contacted Hong Kong Airport for comment and is yet to hear back. So for now, the photo remains a mystery. The bustling Hong Kong Airport. Source: News Limited
